race.comment: NICCONIUM (3) gave away a considerable start over 1350m at Doomben last time before hitting the line well beaten 3l. Has his first crack at the mile and gives every impression it will suit. Finds easier company and the 2kg claim is handy. MUCHACHO (2) was in contention all the way placing second last start over 1500m at Kilcoy. Just missed at Dalby prior and is drawn for a good trail just off the pace. Expect another decent effort. ON ANY TUESDAY (8) is an improver from the Kris Lees yard. Looked a run short at Ballina last time and sits at the bottom of the weights. An awkward gate needs managing.  DON'T STOP ME NOW (5) turned in a nice effort last time out beaten 1.5L at Dalby over 1400m. Likely improver who has been kept on the fresh side.
